  "id": "ALAS2023-2026-1753",
  "title": "Amazon Linux 2023 - ALAS2023-2026-1753: Important priority package update for kernel6.12",
  "issued": {
    "date": "2026-05-25 09:00:00"
  },
  "updated": {
    "date": "2026-06-03 20:58:00"
  },
  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2023 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2026-46333:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nptrace: slightly saner 'get_dumpable()' logic\n\nCVE-2026-43494:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet/rds: reset op_nents when zerocopy page pin fails\n\nCVE-2026-43109:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nx86: shadow stacks: proper error handling for mmap lock\n\nCVE-2026-31716:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfs/ntfs3: validate rec-\u003eused in journal-replay file record check\n\nCVE-2026-31709:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nsmb: client: validate the whole DACL before rewriting it in cifsacl\n\nCVE-2026-31700:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet/packet: fix TOCTOU race on mmap'd vnet_hdr in tpacket_snd()\n\nCVE-2026-31694:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfuse: reject oversized dirents in page cache\n\nCVE-2026-31456:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmm/pagewalk: fix race between concurrent split and refault\n",
